snippet.textDisplay:
The treatment of both the poems didn't work for me. As much as I love Farid Ayaz and Abu Muhammad I felt like they weren't even prepared for this, Natasha sounded more powerful than them. The chorus in the first part didn't go with Natasha, they failed to achieve the feel of those words in their voices, it sounded like that mediocre/funny Qawali in Bollywood movies. Also, it reminded me of Tina Sani's "Mori Araj Suno" from season 03, what a piece. Tina in Mori Araj Suno makes you feel every word of it.
I love coke studio and I expected way more than this when I saw Farid Ayaz and group's names for this season. Well desperately waiting for other pieces.
snippet.textOriginal:
